skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title State Machine - bds/BdsInstance
skinparam state {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
}
left to right direction
hide empty description
state "Observe" as observe
state "EvaluateReady" as evaluate_ready
state "Ready" as ready
state "Retryable" as retryable
state "Failed" as failed
observe : read spec, tracked status, delete intent,\nand current OCI lifecycle
state "ResolveByLookup" as resolve_by_lookup
state "RejectUnsupportedDrift" as reject_unsupported_drift
state "ApplyUpdate" as apply_update
state "DeletePending" as delete_pending
state "Deleted" as deleted
state "DeleteCleanupBlocked" as delete_cleanup_blocked
[*] --> observe : AddKafka, AddWorkerNodes (+1\nmore)
observe --> resolve_by_lookup : tracked identity missing
resolve_by_lookup --> evaluate_ready : lookup or create reaches\nACTIVE, INACTIVE, SUSPENDED
resolve_by_lookup --> retryable : OCI state in CREATING,\nRESUMING, SUSPENDING,\nUPDATING (+1 more)
resolve_by_lookup --> failed : unresolved OCI error or non-success state
observe --> evaluate_ready : OCI state in ACTIVE,\nINACTIVE, SUSPENDED
observe --> retryable : OCI state in CREATING,\nRESUMING, SUSPENDING,\nUPDATING (+1 more)
observe --> failed : unresolved OCI error or non-success state
evaluate_ready --> reject_unsupported_drift : force-new or conflicting\ndrift detected
reject_unsupported_drift --> ready : wait for spec or live state change
evaluate_ready --> apply_update : supported mutable drift for\nbootstrap_script_url,\ndefined_tags, display_name\n(+2 more)
apply_update --> ready : update path completes
evaluate_ready --> ready : no supported drift remains
ready --> ready : no supported drift remains
retryable --> retryable : OCI remains retryable
failed --> failed : OCI remains terminal
ready --> delete_pending : delete requested
retryable --> delete_pending : delete requested
failed --> delete_pending : delete requested
delete_pending --> delete_cleanup_blocked : cleanup or finalizer release remains blocked
delete_cleanup_blocked --> deleted : retry delete completion until allowed
deleted --> deleted : terminal stutter
note right of ready
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-controller-state-machine.svg
Start from the shared controller phase model and
specialize imported provider states, delete
targets, and failure exits here.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers map provider states into the shared
controller phases with explicit finalizer and
requeue policies.
service: bds
slug: bdsinstance
kind: BdsInstance
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required /
retain-until-confirmed-delete
requeue: provisioning, updating, terminating
provider states: create CREATING; update
RESUMING, SUSPENDING, UPDATING; delete DELETING
follow-up: create=read-after-write;
update=read-after-write; delete=confirm-delete
supported drift: bootstrap_script_url,
defined_tags, display_name, freeform_tags (+1
more)
reject before mutate: force-new fields
cluster_profile, cluster_version,
compartment_id, is_high_availability (+3 more)
create-only fields: bds_cluster_version_summary,
cluster_admin_password, cluster_public_key,
kerberos_realm_name (+2 more)
list lookup: oci_bds_bds_instances filters
compartment_id, display_name, state
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
Generated runtime uses read-after-write
follow-up for create and update plus
confirm-delete for delete; `CREATING` maps to
provisioning, `UPDATING`/`SUSPENDING`/`RESUMING`
to updating, `ACTIVE`/`INACTIVE`/`SUSPENDED` to
success, `DELETING` to terminating, and `FAILED`
to the terminal failed bucket.
Pre-create lookup queries `ListBdsInstances`
with `compartmentId` and `displayName`; delete
fallback can re-resolve the tracked cluster
through `ListBdsInstances` when `GetBdsInstance`
stops finding the resource.
Only `displayName`, `bootstrapScriptUrl`,
`freeformTags`, `definedTags`, and `kmsKeyId`
reconcile in place. `compartmentId`,
`clusterVersion`, `isHighAvailability`,
`isSecure`, `clusterProfile`, `networkConfig`,
and `nodes` remain replacement-only drift.
`secretId`, `isSecretReused`,
`bdsClusterVersionSummary`,
`clusterAdminPassword`, `clusterPublicKey`, and
`kerberosRealmName` stay create-only for the
reviewed runtime,
`timeEarliestCertificateExpiration` stays
observed status-only, and the runtime has no
secret side effects.
end note
note right of delete_pending
delete policy: required
delete observe: GetBdsInstance or
ListBdsInstances
delete targets: DELETED
end note
@enduml
